<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1437,1324,2007]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis box="[151,233,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Leaves</emphasis>
pinnae 6(3‚Äì42) per side of rachis. 
<emphasis box="[642,810,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Inflorescences</emphasis>
rachillae 11(3‚Äì32), 2.9(1.1‚Äì4.4) mm in diameter, not hairy, not filiform and not or scarcely narrowed between the flower pits; proximal and distal lips drying darker brown than the rachillae; triads mostly spirally arranged.
